The moral of this story is, I accomplished to do something so weird, my family totally forgot the totally fucked up thing I did
In the midst of the bag of beans fiasco, they completely forgot that I stole liquor from my grandparents.
...it suddenly dawns on me. I NEVER got in trouble for the shit ton of alcohol I stole.
Fast forward about a week later. The subject of the beans comes up again.  As the family is having a good laugh at my expense...
"Yes, she put the beans in a bag! How weird is that?
The rest of the evening is spent calling my grandparents, aunts, uncles and telling them that, Hollyn did the weirdest thing today..."
They cant get over how weird that is.
My parents call my brother outside and the 3 of them stand there and make fun of me for putting the beans in the bag. They laugh at me
They cant wrap their heads around the fact that without a suitable container, I would put re fried beans in a bag
But..you put it in a bag?
Re-fried beans.  Ok...but why are they in a bag??  I explain that I couldnt find a container so I used a bag
And then...she comes across the bag of beans. Her face goes from anger to utter confusion.  What the...What the fuck is this?
With every bottle they pull out, I can see the anger and disappointment growing. I can tell that I am in for it. They are so mad
"I cant believe you stole from your grandparents! Shes furious. My dad is furious, Theyre both yelling.
What the hell is in your purse? Im so busted. My mom grabs my purse and finds all the liquor. What the fuck Hollyn?"
We get home. As Im getting out of the car, the stuff in my overloaded purse shifts, and one of the water bottles becomes visible.
I stuff the bottles and the beans in my purse. My parents arrived. Didnt even notice I was slightly buzzed.
I decided to take them home too. But alas, I could not find a container big enough. No big deal. Ill just use a freezer bag.
I found some empty water bottles and filled them up with alcohol to save for later.  Having not quite finished the refried beans...
Pretty soon, it became time for my parents to pick me up. But I hadnt gotten my fill of drinking.
I spent the afternoon drinking and watching TV. It was great. At one point, I got hungry, so I made myself to refried beans and chips
Im talking vodka, rum, gin...the works.   My mom dropped me off for the afternoon, and I proceeded to raid the liquor cabinet.
Being 15, I had recently discovered the wonders of liquor, and it just so happened that my grandparents kept a fully stocked liquor cabinet.
You can go watch TV at your grandparents house. Fine.
My brother wanted to watch football, I did not. My mom had an idea. Our grandparents lived down the road, and were out of town.
Story time: 18 years ago, I did something. Something my family will never let me live down. I was 15 years old. It began with an argument.
